<dl id="n12216b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12216b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12216b"> 216(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &lsquo;hero&rsquo; of novel / plot</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mais ces h&eacute;ros sont des masques et les h&eacute;ros en g&eacute;n&eacute;ral sont des personnages dont la figuration est un jeu. Le langage en somme dit juste, qui d&eacute;signe d&apos;un m&ecirc;me mot les h&eacute;ros du culte et ceux de la litt&eacute;rature <br><font color="green">[But these heroes are masks and heroes in general are characters whose figuration is a game. In the end, language is correct when it uses a single word to denote <mark>the heroes of a cult and those of literature</mark>]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) XCII</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
